    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, powered by the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains its factory forced-induction plumbing, ensuring the secondary hit of boost remains predictable and strong. The powerplant is mated to a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, providing exceptional torque vectoring and rear-end stability. Recent preventative maintenance includes a full cooling system refresh and a verified compression test on both rotors, confirming the health of the apex seals. The double-wishbone aluminum suspension remains tight, offering the telepathic turn-in these chassis are known for. While the aesthetics reflect a well-maintained driver\u2019s car rather than a museum piece, the mechanical synchronization and structural rigidity are top-tier for its class.",
